  <static seed="118" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberMultiplicationWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>A cake recipe needs <m>{1{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> cups of flour. Using this recipe, to bake <m>9</m> cakes, how many cups of flour are needed?</p>
<p>To bake <m>9</m> cakes, <fillin characters="9" name="AnSwEr0001"/> cups of flour are needed.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>13{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Each cake needs <m>{1{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> cups of flour. To find how many cups of flour are needed to bake <m>9</m> cakes, we use multiplication:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {1{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}} \cdot 9
      \amp = \frac{3}{2} \cdot \frac{9}{1} \\
      
      \amp = \frac{27}{2} \\
      \amp = {13{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>To bake <m>9</m> cakes, <m>{13{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> cups of flour are needed.</p>
</solution>
